{
  "slug": "moral-reasoning-stages",
  "type": "html",
  "title": "Developmental Reinterpretation",
  "concept": "The same behavior gets reinterpreted as you develop the cognitive tools to see what the behavior expresses—what looks like interference at one stage looks like principle at another.",
  "interactiveId": "69599ca0-0fd8-41dc-a92b-5182ff6c9caf",
  "sourcePieceId": "06687efd-3af7-490c-9f30-3d35f7f0f913",
  "publishedAt": 1778453060282,
  "voiceScore": 90,
  "qualityFlag": "low",
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Developmental Reinterpretation</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --stage1: #e8a87c;\n    --stage2: #c27ba0;\n    --stage3: #6a9fb5;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--stage3);\n    min-width: 140px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 7ch;\n    text-align: right;\n  }\n  .scenario {\n    margin: 20px 0;\n    padding: 16px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n  }\n  .scenario-title {\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n    font-size: 0.95rem;\n    color: var(--muted);\n  }\n  .behavior {\n    margin-bottom: 16px;\n    padding-bottom: 16px;\n    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n    line-height: 1.6;\n  }\n  .interpretation {\n    font-size: 0.95rem;\n    line-height: 1.6;\n  }\n  .interpretation strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  .stage-badge {\n    display: inline-block;\n    padding: 3px 10px;\n    border-radius: 3px;\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    text-transform: uppercase;\n    letter-spacing: 0.05em;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n  }\n  .stage-1 { background: var(--stage1); color: #fff; }\n  .stage-2 { background: var(--stage2); color: #fff; }\n  .stage-3 { background: var(--stage3); color: #fff; }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  .stage-track {\n    display: flex;\n    gap: 8px;\n    margin: 20px 0;\n    align-items: center;\n  }\n  .stage-marker {\n    flex: 1;\n    padding: 10px;\n    border: 2px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    text-align: center;\n    transition: all 180ms ease-out;\n    opacity: 0.3;\n    font-weight: 500;\n  }\n  .stage-marker.active {\n    opacity: 1;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    transform: scale(1.05);\n  }\n  .stage-marker.s1 { border-color: var(--stage1); }\n  .stage-marker.s2 { border-color: var(--stage2); }\n  .stage-marker.s3 { border-color: var(--stage3); }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .control {\n      flex-direction: column;\n      align-items: stretch;\n    }\n    .control output {\n      text-align: left;\n    }\n    .stage-track {\n      flex-direction: column;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Drag to shift the developmental stage</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">Same behavior. Different cognitive tools to see what it expresses.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control\">\n  <label for=\"stage\">Stage:</label>\n  <input id=\"stage\" type=\"range\" min=\"1\" max=\"3\" value=\"1\" step=\"1\" aria-describedby=\"stage-out\">\n  <output id=\"stage-out\" for=\"stage\">Early</output>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"stage-track\">\n  <div class=\"stage-marker s1\" id=\"marker-1\">Self-interest</div>\n  <div class=\"stage-marker s2\" id=\"marker-2\">Social roles</div>\n  <div class=\"stage-marker s3\" id=\"marker-3\">Principles</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"scenario\">\n  <div class=\"scenario-title\">What you see:</div>\n  <div class=\"behavior\">An adult stops what they're doing to help someone else. You have to wait.</div>\n  <span class=\"stage-badge\" id=\"stage-badge\">Early Stage</span>\n  <div class=\"interpretation\" id=\"interpretation-text\"></div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\"></p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var slider = document.getElementById('stage');\n    var stageOut = document.getElementById('stage-out');\n    var stageBadge = document.getElementById('stage-badge');\n    var interpretationText = document.getElementById('interpretation-text');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n    var markers = {\n      1: document.getElementById('marker-1'),\n      2: document.getElementById('marker-2'),\n      3: document.getElementById('marker-3')\n    };\n\n    var stages = {\n      1: {\n        label: 'Early',\n        badgeText: 'Early Stage',\n        badgeClass: 'stage-1',\n        interpretation: '<strong>\"Why are we stopping? I want to go.\"</strong> The adult\\'s choice delays what you want. The other person\\'s need is invisible. What registers is: you had a plan, and now you have to wait. The adult is choosing someone else over you. That reads as unfair—not because you can see both sides and judge the trade-off, but because your side is the only one you can see.',\n        caption: 'The behavior looks like interference. You lack the cognitive tools to see what the adult is prioritizing.'\n      },\n      2: {\n        label: 'Middle',\n        badgeText: 'Middle Stage',\n        badgeClass: 'stage-2',\n        interpretation: '<strong>\"Helpful people do this.\"</strong> The adult is acting the way helpful people act. You recognize the behavior fits a social category—being kind, being neighborly, being responsible. You might still wish they\\'d chosen differently, but the action makes sense now. It\\'s what someone in their role does. The behavior isn\\'t interference anymore; it\\'s meeting an expectation.',\n        caption: 'The behavior looks like a social norm. You can see it as part of a role, even if you don\\'t yet see the principle.'\n      },\n      3: {\n        label: 'Later',\n        badgeText: 'Later Stage',\n        badgeClass: 'stage-3',\n        interpretation: '<strong>\"That\\'s who they are.\"</strong> The adult is acting on a value they hold—that when someone needs help and you can give it, you do. You see the behavior as expressing a principle, independent of reward or approval. The choice to help isn\\'t about you, and it isn\\'t about the role. It\\'s about integrity. The same action that once felt like an obstacle now looks like character.',\n        caption: 'The behavior looks like principle. You have the tools to see what it expresses, not just what it costs you.'\n      }\n    };\n\n    function update() {\n      var level = +slider.value;\n      var data = stages[level];\n      stageOut.textContent = data.label;\n      stageBadge.textContent = data.badgeText;\n      stageBadge.className = 'stage-badge ' + data.badgeClass;\n      interpretationText.innerHTML = data.interpretation;\n      caption.textContent = data.caption;\n\n      for (var i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {\n        if (i === level) {\n          markers[i].classList.add('active');\n        } else {\n          markers[i].classList.remove('active');\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    slider.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
